{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to team-lead's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "chinese-phil-expert",
    "senderColor": "cyan",
    "target": "@team-lead",
    "targetColor": "red",
    "summary": "No — keep First/Second/Zeroth numbering",
    "content": "**No.** Keep First/Second/Zeroth. The proposal creates more problems than it solves.\n\n**Problem 1: \"Ultimate Reality\" contradicts the author's own caveat.** Footnote 25 explicitly says 第一实在 is just a name, not an ontological claim. \"Ultimate Reality\" is the most ontologically loaded phrase in all of philosophy -- it is precisely what the author spends the entire 后形而上学 essay arguing we cannot reach. Calling phenomena \"Ultimate Reality\" would make it sound like the author is claiming phenomena ARE the ultimate ground of being, when the author is actually saying: phenomena are simply where we *start*, with no ontological verdict attached.\n\n**Problem 2: \"Ultimate Reality\" is already taken.** In Western metaphysics, \"Ultimate Reality\" refers to God, Brahman, the Absolute, the thing-in-itself -- exactly the kind of 第〇实在 the author argues is unreachable. In Chinese philosophy, 终极实在 (which the author uses) is the standard translation of \"Ultimate Reality.\" The author explicitly says 终极实在 is what metaphysics pursues and what nihilism declares lost. Reusing \"Ultimate\" for 第一实在 would collapse the very distinction the author builds the entire framework on.\n\n**Problem 3: \"Secondary\" implies derivative/lesser.** The author's numbering is directional (we start at 1 and move to 2), not hierarchical (1 is not \"better\" than 2). Second Reality is constructed *from* First Reality but is not lesser -- it is where all concepts, science, and understanding live. \"Secondary\" in English carries connotations of \"subordinate\" or \"less important\" that the author does not intend.\n\n**The numbered scheme works precisely because it is neutral.** First/Second/Zeroth carry no philosophical baggage. They tell you the order of encounter (First = what we encounter first; Second = what we construct next; Zeroth = what we posit as prior). The translator's note can explain this ordering. Neutral labels for a system that is deliberately stripping ontological privilege from all levels is exactly right.\n"
  }
}
